overview: The user tasked the agent with reviewing and enhancing a sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent began by performing a detailed analysis
  of the existing implementation against the provided Statement of Work and
  questionnaire specification, identifying several critical gaps. The approach
  involved systematically addressing these gaps, starting with high-priority
  items. Key decisions included integrating a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with
  immediate safety warnings for high scores, adding explicit detection and
  tailored recommendations for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and incorporating a dedicated section for
  external resource links. Additionally, the agent implemented a weighted
  scoring mechanism for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) to provide more
  accurate assessments. The outcome is a more robust and comprehensive sleep
  questionnaire that better meets the specified acceptance criteria and provides
  more actionable insights to users.
